SCM integration (auto-detects GitHub/GitLab from remote):
.PP
All bindings below automatically detect the SCM platform by inspecting the
.B origin
remote URL. If it contains
.IR github.com ,
the
.B gh
CLI is used; otherwise the
.B glab
CLI is used (supporting both gitlab.com and self-hosted GitLab instances).
This means the same keybinding works regardless of which platform hosts the
repository \(em no configuration needed.
.TP
.B go
Open the repository homepage in your default browser. Useful for quickly
jumping to the project page to check settings, wiki, or README.
Uses
.IR "gh browse" \ or\ "glab repo view --web" .
.TP
.B gp
View the pull request (GitHub) or merge request (GitLab) associated with the
current branch in your browser. Handy to check review status, CI results, or
comment threads without leaving the terminal.
Uses
.IR "gh pr view --web" \ or\ "glab mr view --web" .
.TP
.B gP
Create a new pull request or merge request for the current branch. Opens the
creation form in the browser pre-filled with the branch info, so you can add
a description and reviewers.
Uses
.IR "gh pr create --web" \ or\ "glab mr create --web" .
.TP
.B gw
Open the currently selected commit in the browser. Select a commit in the main
or log view, then press
.B gw
to see its full diff, comments, and CI status on the web interface.
Uses
.IR "gh browse <commit>" \ or\ "glab repo view --web -b <commit>" .
.TP
.B gl
List all open pull requests (GitHub) or merge requests (GitLab) for the
repository directly in the terminal. Displays title, author, and status for
a quick overview of pending work.
Uses
.IR "gh pr list" \ or\ "glab mr list" .
.TP
.B gs
Show CI/CD pipeline status for the current branch. On GitHub, lists recent
workflow runs; on GitLab, opens the pipeline viewer. Useful to check if your
latest push passed or failed without leaving tig.
Uses
.IR "gh run list -b <branch>" \ or\ "glab ci view" .
