.SH QUICK REFERENCE
Environment-specific tips:
.TP
.B ZSH
Use <Up>/<Down> for history substring search, <C-R> for history search
.TP
.B FZF
<C-T> for files, <C-C> for directories (if fzf is installed)
.TP
.B TMUX
<C-A> is the prefix key (replaces <C-B>). Many commands work without prefix.
<C-A> f for FZF session/window switcher, <C-A> g for Claude sessions browser.
.TP
.B TIG
F to fetch, P to push, c for cog commit, go/gp/gl for SCM (auto-detects gh/glab), D for delta diff.
.TP
.B NEOVIM
<space> is the leader key. <C-s> to save, K for LSP hover, <Tab> for completion, <space> for which-key popup.
